+
+**Symptoms:**
+- Desktop: Works fine, database updates sync to Google Drive
+- Laptop: [Describe symptoms when you encounter them]
+
+**Possible Causes:**
+1. Google Drive path different on laptop (`C:\Users\[different_username]\My Drive\...`)
+2. Google Drive Desktop not installed/configured on laptop
+3. Sync folder not set up correctly
+4. Path permissions issue
+
+**What to Check:**
+```bash
+# On laptop, check these paths:
+dir "C:\Users\briah\My Drive\TimeTrackerApp\data\time_tracker.db"
+dir "C:\Users\[laptop_username]\My Drive\TimeTrackerApp\data\time_tracker.db"
+```
+
+**Fix Strategy:**
+1. Verify Google Drive Desktop installed on laptop
+2. Confirm Google Drive path on laptop (may be different username)
+3. Update `config.py` with correct laptop path OR use environment variable
+4. Test database access before running app
